h3. Summary

The current warning about data overwrite for users performing import is rather insufficient. The warning should state that the import will overwrite all JIRA data including the current userbase which will affect other application in the same subscription e.g. Confluence.

Current message:
{noformat}
Please note that this process will delete all existing JIRA data in your site and replace it with data from the selected file. If you only want to import specific content (such as attachments, avatars, or logos) without deleting all site data, you must make sure that you upload a file with those entities only.
{noformat}

The message seems to be focusing on JIRA only and it doesn't mention about userbase overwrite which can affect other running applications.

h3. Suggestion

All critical information that are related to data overwrite should be warned specifically in the first step of import process as this can be destructive. Further details can be further communicated in documentation.

