h3. Problem Definition:
Currently the Supported platforms Documentation for 7.3:
- https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AdminJIRAServer073/Supported+platforms

Under Supported Versions:
{quote}
- JIRA Software 7.2.3 and above
- JIRA Service Desk 3.2.3 and above
{quote}

Under Notes List:
{quote}
- We support the listed JIRA applications when implemented via [AWS CloudFormation templates|https://aws.amazon.com/quickstart/architecture/jira/].
- See [Recommendations for running JIRA Software Data Center in AWS|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AdminJIRAServer073/Recommendations+for+running+JIRA+Software+Data+Center+in+AWS].
{quote}

The [AWS CloudFormation templates|https://aws.amazon.com/quickstart/architecture/jira/] Only Includes Instructions for Datacenter versions of JIRA and Service Desk, Configured using PostgreSQL on Amazon RDS but causes confusion as the Noted Versions do not indicate Datacenter Vs. Standalone

h3. Suggested Solution
change the listed supported Versions to:
{quote}
- JIRA Software Datacenter 7.2.3 and above using PostgreSQL on Amazon RDS
- JIRA Service Desk Datacenter 3.2.3 and above using PostgreSQL on Amazon RDS
{quote}

