Summary: *Please create an iPad-specific version of the JIRA Cloud app.*

 

You really need to create a *dedicated iPad* "JIRA Cloud" app, not just have an app that is native to the iPhone and that _happens_ to run on the iPad.  It's really quite terrible seeing a tiny iPhone centered in my large iPad screen - and even if I 2x the image, it then looks blocky and not at all optimized for the iPad.  It's a real shame that Atlassian hasn't yet created a dedicated iPad app with all the real estate that is available on the iPad vs. the iPhone.  It has been nearly a year, and the JIRA Cloud app seems relatively stable – it's time to create an app for the iPad, even if it has exactly the same features.  It should be pretty quick to do so at this point.

